cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a new motion representation for video enhancement tasks and uses a neural network to learn it in a self-supervised manner. The paper focuses on low-level video processing tasks such as frame interpolation, video denoising/deblocking, and video super-resolution. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, so it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with motion estimation, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics).
